Yellow fever, suspected - Brazil (South): not 20010918.2259
Date: Wed, 19 Sep 2001 09:57:59 +0200
From: Stephen A. Berger, M.D. <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON [edited
<http://www.GideonOnline.com>

Some background data on leptospirosis in Brazil
-----------------------------------------------
Urban epidemics have been reported during the rainy season (April to
August) since the 1970's.
Time period / No. reported / Other info
1986-1995 / 25 482 / 2966 fatal
1987 / 23 / Sao Paulo (from swimming in a pool filled with river water)
1988 / 2005 / 1613 from Rio de Janeiro
1992-1996 / 9755 / --
1996 / 1425 / from Rio de Janeiro; 22 fatal
An outbreak of 326 cases (50 fatal) was reported in Salvador through active
case finding during January to August 1996 - for a local rate of 12.5/100
000. _Leptospira interrogans_ serovar copenhageni was identified in 87% of
cases.
Year / fatal cases reported
1991 / 375
1992 / 340
1993 / 265
1994 / 350
1995 / 425
1996 / 455
1997 / 389
1998 / 396
The principal hosts in this country are rodents, pigs, and dogs; 39% of
rats in Rio de Janeiro are infected.
The principal pathogens in this country are _Leptospira_ serovars
icterohaemorrhagiae, grippotyphosa, canicola, javanica, ballum, and pomona.
